#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:288
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now that the filesystem was created, I could mount it at\n"
"<path>/mnt/newhome</path>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:292
#, no-wrap
msgid "Mounting the new volume"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:293
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>mkdir /mnt/newhome</i>\n"
"# <i>mount /dev/main/lv_home /mnt/newhome</i>\n"
"# <i>df</i>\n"
"Filesystem           1k-blocks      Used Available Use% Mounted on\n"
"/dev/hda3              9765200   6989840   2775360  72% /\n"
"tmpfs                   291388         0    291388   0% /dev/shm\n"
"/dev/main/lv_home      8388348     32840   8355508   1% /mnt/newhome\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:303
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"As you can see above, I was almost ready to copy over all my data in\n"
"<path>/home</path>. Before I began, I dropped to runlevel 1 to ensure that no\n"
"users or processes would be accessing or modifying files in <path>/home</path>\n"
"as they were being copied over:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:309
#, no-wrap
msgid "Runlevel 1"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:310
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>init 1</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:314
#, no-wrap
msgid "Then, I began copying the files:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:317
#, no-wrap
msgid "Copying files to the new directory"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:318
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>cp -avx /home/* /mnt/newhome</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:322
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The copy completed in about ten minutes. Then, I backed up my original\n"
"<path>/home</path> to <path>/home.old</path>, just in case something was wrong\n"
"with my copy. I created a new mount point, and remounted the new home at\n"
"<path>/home</path>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:328
#, no-wrap
msgid "The new mount point"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:329
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>cd /</i>\n"
"# <i>mv home home.old</i>\n"
"# <i>mkdir home</i>\n"
"# <i>umount /mnt/newhome</i>\n"
"# <i>mount /dev/main/lv_home /home</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:337
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Then, it was time to set up the server so that my new <path>/home</path>\n"
"partition would be available every time the machine started up. First, I\n"
"modified my <path>/etc/fstab</path> so that it included a new\n"
"<path>/home</path> entry:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:343
#, no-wrap
msgid "Editing fstab"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:344
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>\n"
"#fs                 mountpoint       type         opts          dump/pass</comment>\n"
"/dev/hda3           /                reiserfs     defaults      1 1\n"
"/dev/main/lv_home   /home            reiserfs     defaults      2 2\n"
"/dev/hda2           none             swap         sw            0 0\n"
"/dev/hda1           /boot            reiserfs     noauto        0 0\n"
"/dev/cdrom          /mnt/cdrom       iso9660      noauto,ro     0 0\n"
"proc                /proc            proc         defaults      0 0\n"
"none                /dev/pts         devpts       mode=620      0 0\n"
"tmpfs               /dev/shm         tmpfs        defaults      0 0\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:357
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Then, I made minor modifications to my initialization scripts. I modified my\n"
"\"checkroot\" startup script so that the following commands would run immediately\n"
"after my root partition was remounted read/write:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:362
#, no-wrap
msgid "Modifying the startup script"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:363
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"/sbin/vgscan\n"
"/sbin/vgchange -a y\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:368
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Then, I modified my filesystem unmounting script that gets run on shutdown, so\n"
"that the following command would run immediately after all filesystems were\n"
"unmounted:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:373
#, no-wrap
msgid "Modifying the shutdown script"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:374
#, no-wrap
msgid "/sbin/vgchange -a n\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:378
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Once I had completed these steps, I rebooted the machine, and to my delight\n"
"everything worked perfectly. After a day or so of absolutely no problems, I\n"
"deleted <path>/home.old</path> to free up some space on my root filesystem.\n"
"Yay! The transition to LVM was a success.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:387
#, no-wrap
msgid "The beauty of LVM"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:391
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"While the transition to LVM is a bit of an ordeal, once the transition is\n"
"complete, managing filesystems becomes tremendously easier. As an example, I\n"
"decided to resize my new <path>/home</path> logical volume, adding about 2\n"
"gigabytes worth of space to the end of the filesystem. First, I added\n"
"additional capacity to my \"lv_home\" logical volume, and then I used the\n"
"<c>resize_reiserfs</c> utility to expand the filesystem so that it would use\n"
"this additional capacity. Here are the two commands that did all this:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:400
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using additional space"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:401
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>lvextend -L+2G /dev/main/lv_home</i>\n"
"# <i>resize_reiserfs -f /dev/main/lv_home</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:406
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In about a second, I had enlarged my <path>/home</path> filesystem by 2 GB;\n"
"amazingly, I didn't need to reboot, drop to runlevel 1, or even unmount\n"
"<path>/home</path> to perform the resize. Everything continued to work as it\n"
"had before. Isn't that great? Here's the current state of my filesystems:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:412
#, no-wrap
msgid "Filesystem space"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:413
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>df</i>\n"
"Filesystem           1k-blocks      Used Available Use% Mounted on\n"
"/dev/hda3              9765200   1413340   8351860  15% /\n"
"/dev/main/lv_home     10485436   5609836   4875600  54% /home\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:420
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can see how LVM really can make an administrator's work a whole lot easier.\n"
"In the future, I hope to move additional parts of my root filesystem over to\n"
"LVM, and eventually even convert my root filesystem over to an LVM logical\n"
"volume. The resources below will help you learn even more about LVM.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:429
#, no-wrap
msgid "Resources"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/articles/lvm-p2.xml:434
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
